<Layout title="Resources" description="How to actually farm resources in Last War: Survival at HQ 15–30 — with honest flags on what the community data can and cannot back up.">
  <h1>Resources</h1>
  <p class="text-lg text-[#8a96b0]">Farming resources well is less about a secret number and more about timing: open chests when they'll score, and don't trust a static cost table that doesn't exist. Last verified: July 2026.</p>

  <QuickSummary>
    <p><strong>The short version:</strong> Doom Elites with Monica are the best per-stamina farming target — the exact bonus % is disputed between sources, so check your own in-game tooltip. Build Arms Race chests and packages ahead of time, but <strong>open them during the matching phase</strong> — points post on open, not on completion, which reverses the old "save pops for the final hours" advice. There's no public gear-ore or skill-medal cost table; use an interactive calculator instead of a guessed number. Everything else on this page below is flagged with how solid the sourcing actually is.</p>
  </QuickSummary>

  <h2>Doom Elite Farming with Monica</h2>
  <p class="text-sm">Hero Monica applies a farming bonus against Doom Elites (also called Ironhead, Glutton, or Miser depending on the elite type — all Last War-specific names, not shared with other games). The mechanic itself is solid: bring Monica to a Doom Elite fight and your resource return goes up. <strong>The size of that bonus is genuinely disputed</strong> between the two sources that cover it:</p>
  <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
    <li><strong>lastwartutorial.com</strong> reports a flat <strong>39%</strong> bonus.</li>
    <li><strong>theriagames.com</strong> reports a base of roughly <strong>30.9%, scaling up by about 5% per star</strong> on Monica.</li>
  </ul>
  <p class="text-sm">These aren't the same claim wearing different clothes — one is a flat number, the other scales with Monica's star level. This page won't launder either into a single settled figure. <strong>Check your own in-game tooltip on Monica's skill</strong> for the number that actually applies on your server/patch. (An older figure of 25% circulating elsewhere traces back to an unattributed aggregator site — don't use it.)</p>
  <p class="text-sm text-[#8a96b0]">What we don't have a source for: any star or skill-level threshold for when Monica becomes "worth it," how rally rewards get split among participants, stamina cost per rally, or whether stacking multiple Monicas compounds the bonus. The one weak signal available (single low-tier source) suggests the bonus attaches to whoever holds Monica, not to the whole rally — so don't assume non-Monica participants share in it. Treat all of this as pending verification rather than settled mechanics, and don't port stamina-split rules from other rally events (like General's Trial) onto Doom Elites — there's no source tying the two together.</p>

  <h2>Arms Race Chest Timing</h2>
  <p class="text-sm">This is the one piece of old advice on this page that was flatly wrong, and it's worth stating plainly: <strong>Arms Race points post when an item is opened, not when it's completed or earned</strong> (single-sourced: lastwartutorial.com, Tier 1 — cross-check in-game before planning around it). That means the correct play is:</p>
  <ol class="list-decimal pl-5 text-sm space-y-1">
    <li>Finish builds, research, training, and other progress as normal — but leave the resulting chests/packages <strong>unopened and packaged</strong>.</li>
    <li>Open them once the Arms Race board is showing the <strong>matching phase</strong> (e.g., open a completed-building gift box during a Base Building phase, open troop-training rewards during Unit Progression).</li>
  </ol>
  <p class="text-sm">The old "save every pop for the final hours" advice this page used to give has no basis in that mechanic and is being dropped. There's also no source anywhere for a "synchronize alliance-wide simultaneous opens for a bonus" mechanic — treat that as a myth, not a strategy. The real adjacent trick is individual, not alliance-wide: match your own Arms Race phase opening to that day's VS theme so one action scores in both events at once. See the <a href="/events" class="text-[#f59e0b] hover:underline">events page</a> for the VS day-by-day schedule and how the two events line up.</p>
  <p class="text-sm text-[#8a96b0]">The six rotating ~4-hour Arms Race phases and their names (Base Building, Unit Progression, Tech Research, Drone Boost, Hero Advancement, City Building) are single-sourced — treat the whole set (count, cycle, and names) as pending a second confirmation rather than settled; check the in-game Arms Race board for your server’s actual rotation.</p>

  <h2>Resource Priorities</h2>
  <p class="text-sm">No public, verified cost table exists for gear ore or skill medals — not on this site, and not anywhere the research turned up. Both cpt-hedge.com and theriagames.com publish <strong>interactive calculators</strong> rather than static tables, because the real costs depend on your specific hero, gear rarity, and current level. That's the honest state of the data: use one of those calculators for numbers, not a guess published here.</p>
  <p class="text-sm">What can be said without inventing a number is qualitative, and it hasn't changed:</p>
  <ol class="list-decimal pl-5 text-sm space-y-1">
    <li><strong>Hero shards</strong> — star-ups are the biggest single power spike per resource spent; prioritize your main squad's core heroes.</li>
    <li><strong>Gear materials and ore</strong> — feed your top few heroes' gear rather than spreading thin; use the calculators above for exact ore counts.</li>
    <li><strong>Skill medals</strong> — max active skills on your primary damage dealer before spreading to secondary heroes.</li>
    <li><strong>Research and troop-related tech</strong> — compounds your output over time rather than giving a one-time spike.</li>
    <li><strong>Food/energy</strong> — hold only what training and healing need; hoarding past that is dead weight.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Stamina and Troop Load</h2>
  <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
    <li><strong>Stamina:</strong> one Tier-3 source (lastwarhandbook.com) reports a cap of 120 and regen of 1 per 300 seconds (12/hour, ~288/day). Tier-3 sources on this site are leads, not confirmations — this number is <span class="text-[#8a96b0]">[VERIFY]</span> and comes from a single source with known content-farm signals. Don't plan a rotation tightly around it; check your own stamina bar's regen rate instead.</li>
    <li><strong>Troop load:</strong> a per-march carry ceiling exists and is raised by troop tiers, Development/Economy research, and gathering-hero gear (per packsify.com, single-source <span class="text-[#8a96b0]">[VERIFY]</span>). Specific per-tier numbers circulating elsewhere (e.g., "Tier 1 = 400 load") don't trace back to that source or any other — they're unsupported and are not repeated here.</li>
  </ul>

  <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-[#8a96b0]">Hoarding resources without spending them on your main squad is one of the slowest ways to progress — that part hasn't changed. What has changed is the timing advice above: open Arms Race chests on-phase, not at the buzzer.</p>

  <p class="mt-4 text-xs text-[#8a96b0]">Sources: lastwartutorial.com (Doom Elite/Monica bonus figure, Arms Race open-to-score mechanic — screenshot-verified, dev-corroborated), theriagames.com (Monica bonus figure, gear-cost calculator), cpt-hedge.com (gear-cost calculator), packsify.com (troop load mechanic, single-source), lastwarhandbook.com (stamina cap/regen, Tier-3 lead only — flagged [VERIFY]). The Monica bonus percentage is presented as disputed because the two sourced figures conflict; check your in-game tooltip. Rally-reward distribution, stamina cost per rally, Monica stacking, and any star/skill threshold for Doom Elites have no reliable source and are stated as unverified rather than guessed. No public static cost table exists for gear ore or skill medals.</p>
</Layout>
